column5: Gotta get an open water salmon some day.  Nice going FreshT!
Nice one...so fresh and so clean
S.
I caught a king this year it was allot smaller then that

Late start to this season, the weather and mechanical issues on the boat held us back.  Went down Friday for the shakedown run,out for 2 hours and got a beauty.  Would have liked to catch this fish a few months from now.   Headed back out sat am  tough bite but went 4/4 2 salmon 2 rainbows .  Bring on summer !
Beauty for sure! Good start man.
That's a fine looking fish.
Beauty! Hows that kicker working for ya?
Nice!
Sweet! Southern shore has been hot this year!  I still haven't made it out, lol
Working good so far... How is the little Johnson working?
Nice fish! I was surprised no report from you till now since you had an early start last year.  Wish you a great year on the water!
Sweet fish bud. Thats a good,n.
show off  nice one to start the year
Glad to hear! I havent even touched the johnson. Its still hanging right where i put it when you brought it here....lol
Right on! Beauty fish
If you feel like selling it let me know.
Come to the dark side.....I mean west end.
I think that this conversation could be deemed "inappropriate"  JK. Nice silver bud
Only you Sy. Lol
I was waiting for that! Get your mind outta the gutter! LOL  Engine is not for sale...its way too handy to get rid of!  S.
That's a really nice, clean fish. Great job.
Tell me about it. I miss it already.
How do you like them dipsies?
Red in particular? Or dipsies in general?   We catch more than 50 percent of our fish on dipsies.
Red in particular? Or dipsies in general? We catch more than 50 percent of our fish on dipsies.  Yeah, dipsies in general. I tend to run them when the water's too rough to mess with riggers.
I always have a dipsie in the water with a paddle and fly.   On sat fish wouldn't touch the riggers dipsies took all 4 fish. Usually run them on a 2 setting with 150- 250 ft of line out
Same here..  2 dipsies with SD/flies, 2 riggers with spoons + cheaters.

I always have a dipsie in the water with a paddle and fly. On sat fish wouldn't touch the riggers dipsies took all 4 fish. Usually run them on a 2 setting with 150- 250 ft of line out that setup was the one that caught both last year when we went.
